    "faqTitle": "Frequently Asked Questions",
    "faqSubtitle": "Everything you need to know about BSQ Portal",
    "faq1Q": "How does the OTP system work?",
    "faq1A": "When a teacher assigns students to an exam, the system generates a unique 6-digit OTP for each student. The school admin views and distributes these codes. Students must enter their OTP before starting the exam — this prevents unauthorized access.",
    "faq2Q": "What happens if a student loses internet during the exam?",
    "faq2A": "Every answer is saved to the server the moment it is selected or typed (with a short debounce for text answers). If a student's connection drops and they return, all their answers are restored exactly as they left them.",
    "faq3Q": "Can teachers grade open-ended answers?",
    "faq3A": "Yes. After a student submits an exam with open questions, the teacher who created the exam can mark each open answer as Correct or Wrong. The system then calculates the final score and grade automatically.",
    "faq4Q": "What is the approval workflow?",
    "faq4A": "After a teacher prepares an exam (questions + students + marks), they submit it for approval. The school admin reviews and either approves (instantly publishing it to students) or rejects it with a note. This ensures quality control.",
    "faq5Q": "How is the countdown timer handled across time zones?",
    "faq5A": "The countdown is computed server-side and delivered as an absolute end timestamp. The frontend adjusts for any difference between the server clock and the student's device clock, so the timer is always accurate regardless of the student's location.",

